<?xml version="1.0" encoding="utf-8" standalone="yes"?><rss version="2.0" xmlns:atom="http://www.w3.org/2005/Atom"><channel><title>Server on ErrorCode — Error Code Reference &amp; Solutions</title><link>https://errorcode.excellentwiki.com/tags/server/</link><description>Recent content in Server on ErrorCode — Error Code Reference &amp; Solutions</description><generator>Hugo</generator><language>en</language><atom:link href="https://errorcode.excellentwiki.com/tags/server/index.xml" rel="self" type="application/rss+xml"/><item><title>[Solution] Linux ECONNREFUSED (errno 75) — Connection Refused Fix</title><link>https://errorcode.excellentwiki.com/os/linux/errno-75/</link><pubDate>Mon, 01 Jan 0001 00:00:00 +0000</pubDate><guid>https://errorcode.excellentwiki.com/os/linux/errno-75/</guid><description>&lt;h1 id="linux-econnrefused-errno-75--connection-refused"&gt;Linux ECONNREFUSED (errno 75) — Connection Refused&lt;/h1&gt;
&lt;p&gt;ECONNREFUSED (errno 75) means the remote host actively refused the connection. This error occurs when a client tries to connect to a port where no server is listening, or the server&amp;rsquo;s backlog queue is full. It is distinct from ETIMEDOUT (errno 74) because ECONNREFUSED means the remote host sent a TCP RST, while ETIMEDOUT means no response was received.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;h2 id="common-causes"&gt;Common Causes&lt;/h2&gt;
&lt;ul&gt;
&lt;li&gt;No server process listening on the target port&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Server process crashed or was not started&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Server backlog queue is full&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Firewall rejecting connections with RST instead of dropping&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;/ul&gt;
&lt;h2 id="how-to-fix-econnrefused"&gt;How to Fix ECONNREFUSED&lt;/h2&gt;
&lt;h3 id="1-verify-server-is-running"&gt;1. Verify Server is Running&lt;/h3&gt;
&lt;p&gt;Check if the server process is active:&lt;/p&gt;</description></item><item><title>[Solution] Python ConnectionRefusedError — Connection Refused Fix</title><link>https://errorcode.excellentwiki.com/languages/python/connectionrefusederror/</link><pubDate>Mon, 01 Jan 0001 00:00:00 +0000</pubDate><guid>https://errorcode.excellentwiki.com/languages/python/connectionrefusederror/</guid><description>&lt;h1 id="connectionrefusederror--connection-refused-fix"&gt;ConnectionRefusedError — Connection Refused Fix&lt;/h1&gt;
&lt;p&gt;A &lt;code&gt;ConnectionRefusedError&lt;/code&gt; is raised when a connection attempt is actively refused by the server. It&amp;rsquo;s a subclass of &lt;code&gt;ConnectionError&lt;/code&gt;, which is a subclass of &lt;code&gt;OSError&lt;/code&gt;. This typically means the server is not running or not listening on the specified port.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;h2 id="description"&gt;Description&lt;/h2&gt;
&lt;p&gt;When you try to connect to a host and port where no service is listening, the operating system&amp;rsquo;s TCP/IP stack responds with a &amp;ldquo;connection refused&amp;rdquo; (RST packet). Python raises &lt;code&gt;ConnectionRefusedError&lt;/code&gt; to indicate this. Unlike a timeout (which means the host is unreachable), a refused connection means the host is reachable but the port is closed.&lt;/p&gt;</description></item><item><title>[Solution] React SSR Hydration Error — Server/Client Mismatch Fix</title><link>https://errorcode.excellentwiki.com/languages/javascript/react-ssr-error/</link><pubDate>Mon, 01 Jan 0001 00:00:00 +0000</pubDate><guid>https://errorcode.excellentwiki.com/languages/javascript/react-ssr-error/</guid><description>&lt;h1 id="react-ssr-hydration-error--serverclient-mismatch"&gt;React SSR Hydration Error — Server/Client Mismatch&lt;/h1&gt;
&lt;p&gt;The error &lt;code&gt;Hydration failed because the initial UI does not match what was rendered on the server&lt;/code&gt; occurs when the server-rendered HTML does not match what React expects during client-side hydration. React detects the mismatch and falls back to client-only rendering.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;h2 id="description"&gt;Description&lt;/h2&gt;
&lt;p&gt;In Server-Side Rendering (SSR), React renders components to HTML on the server, sends it to the client, then &amp;ldquo;hydrates&amp;rdquo; it by attaching event listeners and making it interactive. If the server and client produce different HTML, hydration fails.&lt;/p&gt;</description></item><item><title>Node.js Error: listen EADDRINUSE</title><link>https://errorcode.excellentwiki.com/languages/javascript/node-listen-eaddrinuse/</link><pubDate>Mon, 01 Jan 0001 00:00:00 +0000</pubDate><guid>https://errorcode.excellentwiki.com/languages/javascript/node-listen-eaddrinuse/</guid><description>&lt;p&gt;The &lt;code&gt;EADDRINUSE&lt;/code&gt; error occurs when a Node.js server tries to bind to a port that is already in use by another process. This is one of the most common errors when developing or deploying Node.js applications.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;h2 id="description"&gt;Description&lt;/h2&gt;
&lt;p&gt;Common EADDRINUSE messages include:&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;ul&gt;
&lt;li&gt;&lt;code&gt;Error: listen EADDRINUSE: address already in use :::3000&lt;/code&gt; — port 3000 is taken&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;&lt;code&gt;listen EADDRINUSE 0.0.0.0:80&lt;/code&gt; — port 80 is in use&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;&lt;code&gt;Error: listen EADDRINUSE 127.0.0.1:5432&lt;/code&gt; — port already bound&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;/ul&gt;
&lt;h2 id="common-causes"&gt;Common Causes&lt;/h2&gt;
&lt;div class="highlight"&gt;&lt;pre tabindex="0" style="color:#f8f8f2;background-color:#272822;-moz-tab-size:4;-o-tab-size:4;tab-size:4;-webkit-text-size-adjust:none;"&gt;&lt;code class="language-javascript" data-lang="javascript"&gt;&lt;span style="display:flex;"&gt;&lt;span&gt;&lt;span style="color:#75715e"&gt;// Cause 1: Previous server instance still running
&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span style="display:flex;"&gt;&lt;span&gt;&lt;span style="color:#75715e"&gt;// $ node server.js (crashed but process still in background)
&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span style="display:flex;"&gt;&lt;span&gt;
&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span style="display:flex;"&gt;&lt;span&gt;&lt;span style="color:#75715e"&gt;// Cause 2: Another application uses the same port
&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span style="display:flex;"&gt;&lt;span&gt;&lt;span style="color:#75715e"&gt;// Another Node.js app, Python server, or system service
&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span style="display:flex;"&gt;&lt;span&gt;
&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span style="display:flex;"&gt;&lt;span&gt;&lt;span style="color:#75715e"&gt;// Cause 3: Rapid restart during development
&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span style="display:flex;"&gt;&lt;span&gt;&lt;span style="color:#75715e"&gt;// Port is still in TIME_WAIT state after server closes
&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span style="display:flex;"&gt;&lt;span&gt;
&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span style="display:flex;"&gt;&lt;span&gt;&lt;span style="color:#75715e"&gt;// Cause 4: Multiple workers binding to the same port
&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span style="display:flex;"&gt;&lt;span&gt;&lt;span style="color:#75715e"&gt;// cluster.fork() without sharing the socket handle
&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/code&gt;&lt;/pre&gt;&lt;/div&gt;&lt;h2 id="solutions"&gt;Solutions&lt;/h2&gt;
&lt;h3 id="fix-1-find-and-kill-the-process-using-the-port"&gt;Fix 1: Find and kill the process using the port&lt;/h3&gt;
&lt;div class="highlight"&gt;&lt;pre tabindex="0" style="color:#f8f8f2;background-color:#272822;-moz-tab-size:4;-o-tab-size:4;tab-size:4;-webkit-text-size-adjust:none;"&gt;&lt;code class="language-bash" data-lang="bash"&gt;&lt;span style="display:flex;"&gt;&lt;span&gt;&lt;span style="color:#75715e"&gt;# Find the process using the port&lt;/span&gt;
&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span style="display:flex;"&gt;&lt;span&gt;lsof -i :3000
&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span style="display:flex;"&gt;&lt;span&gt;
&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span style="display:flex;"&gt;&lt;span&gt;&lt;span style="color:#75715e"&gt;# Or with ss&lt;/span&gt;
&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span style="display:flex;"&gt;&lt;span&gt;ss -tlnp | grep &lt;span style="color:#ae81ff"&gt;3000&lt;/span&gt;
&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span style="display:flex;"&gt;&lt;span&gt;
&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span style="display:flex;"&gt;&lt;span&gt;&lt;span style="color:#75715e"&gt;# Kill the process&lt;/span&gt;
&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span style="display:flex;"&gt;&lt;span&gt;kill -9 &lt;span style="color:#66d9ef"&gt;$(&lt;/span&gt;lsof -t -i :3000&lt;span style="color:#66d9ef"&gt;)&lt;/span&gt;
&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/code&gt;&lt;/pre&gt;&lt;/div&gt;&lt;h3 id="fix-2-use-a-dynamic-port-or-so_reuseaddr"&gt;Fix 2: Use a dynamic port or SO_REUSEADDR&lt;/h3&gt;
&lt;div class="highlight"&gt;&lt;pre tabindex="0" style="color:#f8f8f2;background-color:#272822;-moz-tab-size:4;-o-tab-size:4;tab-size:4;-webkit-text-size-adjust:none;"&gt;&lt;code class="language-javascript" data-lang="javascript"&gt;&lt;span style="display:flex;"&gt;&lt;span&gt;&lt;span style="color:#66d9ef"&gt;const&lt;/span&gt; &lt;span style="color:#a6e22e"&gt;http&lt;/span&gt; &lt;span style="color:#f92672"&gt;=&lt;/span&gt; &lt;span style="color:#a6e22e"&gt;require&lt;/span&gt;(&lt;span style="color:#e6db74"&gt;&amp;#34;node:http&amp;#34;&lt;/span&gt;);
&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span style="display:flex;"&gt;&lt;span&gt;
&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span style="display:flex;"&gt;&lt;span&gt;&lt;span style="color:#66d9ef"&gt;const&lt;/span&gt; &lt;span style="color:#a6e22e"&gt;server&lt;/span&gt; &lt;span style="color:#f92672"&gt;=&lt;/span&gt; &lt;span style="color:#a6e22e"&gt;http&lt;/span&gt;.&lt;span style="color:#a6e22e"&gt;createServer&lt;/span&gt;((&lt;span style="color:#a6e22e"&gt;req&lt;/span&gt;, &lt;span style="color:#a6e22e"&gt;res&lt;/span&gt;) =&amp;gt; {
&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span style="display:flex;"&gt;&lt;span&gt; &lt;span style="color:#a6e22e"&gt;res&lt;/span&gt;.&lt;span style="color:#a6e22e"&gt;end&lt;/span&gt;(&lt;span style="color:#e6db74"&gt;&amp;#34;ok&amp;#34;&lt;/span&gt;);
&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span style="display:flex;"&gt;&lt;span&gt;});
&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span style="display:flex;"&gt;&lt;span&gt;
&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span style="display:flex;"&gt;&lt;span&gt;&lt;span style="color:#75715e"&gt;// Let the OS assign a random available port
&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span style="display:flex;"&gt;&lt;span&gt;&lt;span style="color:#a6e22e"&gt;server&lt;/span&gt;.&lt;span style="color:#a6e22e"&gt;listen&lt;/span&gt;(&lt;span style="color:#ae81ff"&gt;0&lt;/span&gt;, () =&amp;gt; {
&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span style="display:flex;"&gt;&lt;span&gt; &lt;span style="color:#a6e22e"&gt;console&lt;/span&gt;.&lt;span style="color:#a6e22e"&gt;log&lt;/span&gt;(&lt;span style="color:#e6db74"&gt;`Listening on port &lt;/span&gt;&lt;span style="color:#e6db74"&gt;${&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span style="color:#a6e22e"&gt;server&lt;/span&gt;.&lt;span style="color:#a6e22e"&gt;address&lt;/span&gt;().&lt;span style="color:#a6e22e"&gt;port&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span style="color:#e6db74"&gt;}&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span style="color:#e6db74"&gt;`&lt;/span&gt;);
&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span style="display:flex;"&gt;&lt;span&gt;});
&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/code&gt;&lt;/pre&gt;&lt;/div&gt;&lt;h3 id="fix-3-handle-the-error-with-retry-logic"&gt;Fix 3: Handle the error with retry logic&lt;/h3&gt;
&lt;div class="highlight"&gt;&lt;pre tabindex="0" style="color:#f8f8f2;background-color:#272822;-moz-tab-size:4;-o-tab-size:4;tab-size:4;-webkit-text-size-adjust:none;"&gt;&lt;code class="language-javascript" data-lang="javascript"&gt;&lt;span style="display:flex;"&gt;&lt;span&gt;&lt;span style="color:#66d9ef"&gt;const&lt;/span&gt; &lt;span style="color:#a6e22e"&gt;http&lt;/span&gt; &lt;span style="color:#f92672"&gt;=&lt;/span&gt; &lt;span style="color:#a6e22e"&gt;require&lt;/span&gt;(&lt;span style="color:#e6db74"&gt;&amp;#34;node:http&amp;#34;&lt;/span&gt;);
&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span style="display:flex;"&gt;&lt;span&gt;
&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span style="display:flex;"&gt;&lt;span&gt;&lt;span style="color:#66d9ef"&gt;function&lt;/span&gt; &lt;span style="color:#a6e22e"&gt;startServer&lt;/span&gt;(&lt;span style="color:#a6e22e"&gt;port&lt;/span&gt;, &lt;span style="color:#a6e22e"&gt;retries&lt;/span&gt; &lt;span style="color:#f92672"&gt;=&lt;/span&gt; &lt;span style="color:#ae81ff"&gt;3&lt;/span&gt;) {
&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span style="display:flex;"&gt;&lt;span&gt; &lt;span style="color:#66d9ef"&gt;const&lt;/span&gt; &lt;span style="color:#a6e22e"&gt;server&lt;/span&gt; &lt;span style="color:#f92672"&gt;=&lt;/span&gt; &lt;span style="color:#a6e22e"&gt;http&lt;/span&gt;.&lt;span style="color:#a6e22e"&gt;createServer&lt;/span&gt;((&lt;span style="color:#a6e22e"&gt;req&lt;/span&gt;, &lt;span style="color:#a6e22e"&gt;res&lt;/span&gt;) =&amp;gt; {
&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span style="display:flex;"&gt;&lt;span&gt; &lt;span style="color:#a6e22e"&gt;res&lt;/span&gt;.&lt;span style="color:#a6e22e"&gt;end&lt;/span&gt;(&lt;span style="color:#e6db74"&gt;&amp;#34;ok&amp;#34;&lt;/span&gt;);
&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span style="display:flex;"&gt;&lt;span&gt; });
&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span style="display:flex;"&gt;&lt;span&gt;
&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span style="display:flex;"&gt;&lt;span&gt; &lt;span style="color:#a6e22e"&gt;server&lt;/span&gt;.&lt;span style="color:#a6e22e"&gt;on&lt;/span&gt;(&lt;span style="color:#e6db74"&gt;&amp;#34;error&amp;#34;&lt;/span&gt;, (&lt;span style="color:#a6e22e"&gt;err&lt;/span&gt;) =&amp;gt; {
&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span style="display:flex;"&gt;&lt;span&gt; &lt;span style="color:#66d9ef"&gt;if&lt;/span&gt; (&lt;span style="color:#a6e22e"&gt;err&lt;/span&gt;.&lt;span style="color:#a6e22e"&gt;code&lt;/span&gt; &lt;span style="color:#f92672"&gt;===&lt;/span&gt; &lt;span style="color:#e6db74"&gt;&amp;#34;EADDRINUSE&amp;#34;&lt;/span&gt; &lt;span style="color:#f92672"&gt;&amp;amp;&amp;amp;&lt;/span&gt; &lt;span style="color:#a6e22e"&gt;retries&lt;/span&gt; &lt;span style="color:#f92672"&gt;&amp;gt;&lt;/span&gt; &lt;span style="color:#ae81ff"&gt;0&lt;/span&gt;) {
&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span style="display:flex;"&gt;&lt;span&gt; &lt;span style="color:#a6e22e"&gt;console&lt;/span&gt;.&lt;span style="color:#a6e22e"&gt;log&lt;/span&gt;(&lt;span style="color:#e6db74"&gt;`Port &lt;/span&gt;&lt;span style="color:#e6db74"&gt;${&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span style="color:#a6e22e"&gt;port&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span style="color:#e6db74"&gt;}&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span style="color:#e6db74"&gt; in use, retrying in 1s...`&lt;/span&gt;);
&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span style="display:flex;"&gt;&lt;span&gt; &lt;span style="color:#a6e22e"&gt;setTimeout&lt;/span&gt;(() =&amp;gt; &lt;span style="color:#a6e22e"&gt;startServer&lt;/span&gt;(&lt;span style="color:#a6e22e"&gt;port&lt;/span&gt; &lt;span style="color:#f92672"&gt;+&lt;/span&gt; &lt;span style="color:#ae81ff"&gt;1&lt;/span&gt;, &lt;span style="color:#a6e22e"&gt;retries&lt;/span&gt; &lt;span style="color:#f92672"&gt;-&lt;/span&gt; &lt;span style="color:#ae81ff"&gt;1&lt;/span&gt;), &lt;span style="color:#ae81ff"&gt;1000&lt;/span&gt;);
&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span style="display:flex;"&gt;&lt;span&gt; } &lt;span style="color:#66d9ef"&gt;else&lt;/span&gt; {
&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span style="display:flex;"&gt;&lt;span&gt; &lt;span style="color:#a6e22e"&gt;console&lt;/span&gt;.&lt;span style="color:#a6e22e"&gt;error&lt;/span&gt;(&lt;span style="color:#e6db74"&gt;`Failed to start server on port &lt;/span&gt;&lt;span style="color:#e6db74"&gt;${&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span style="color:#a6e22e"&gt;port&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span style="color:#e6db74"&gt;}&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span style="color:#e6db74"&gt;:`&lt;/span&gt;, &lt;span style="color:#a6e22e"&gt;err&lt;/span&gt;.&lt;span style="color:#a6e22e"&gt;message&lt;/span&gt;);
&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span style="display:flex;"&gt;&lt;span&gt; &lt;span style="color:#a6e22e"&gt;process&lt;/span&gt;.&lt;span style="color:#a6e22e"&gt;exit&lt;/span&gt;(&lt;span style="color:#ae81ff"&gt;1&lt;/span&gt;);
&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span style="display:flex;"&gt;&lt;span&gt; }
&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span style="display:flex;"&gt;&lt;span&gt; });
&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span style="display:flex;"&gt;&lt;span&gt;
&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span style="display:flex;"&gt;&lt;span&gt; &lt;span style="color:#a6e22e"&gt;server&lt;/span&gt;.&lt;span style="color:#a6e22e"&gt;listen&lt;/span&gt;(&lt;span style="color:#a6e22e"&gt;port&lt;/span&gt;, () =&amp;gt; {
&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span style="display:flex;"&gt;&lt;span&gt; &lt;span style="color:#a6e22e"&gt;console&lt;/span&gt;.&lt;span style="color:#a6e22e"&gt;log&lt;/span&gt;(&lt;span style="color:#e6db74"&gt;`Server running on port &lt;/span&gt;&lt;span style="color:#e6db74"&gt;${&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span style="color:#a6e22e"&gt;port&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span style="color:#e6db74"&gt;}&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span style="color:#e6db74"&gt;`&lt;/span&gt;);
&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span style="display:flex;"&gt;&lt;span&gt; });
&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span style="display:flex;"&gt;&lt;span&gt;}
&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span style="display:flex;"&gt;&lt;span&gt;
&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span style="display:flex;"&gt;&lt;span&gt;&lt;span style="color:#a6e22e"&gt;startServer&lt;/span&gt;(&lt;span style="color:#ae81ff"&gt;3000&lt;/span&gt;);
&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/code&gt;&lt;/pre&gt;&lt;/div&gt;&lt;h3 id="fix-4-use-so_reuseaddr-option"&gt;Fix 4: Use SO_REUSEADDR option&lt;/h3&gt;
&lt;div class="highlight"&gt;&lt;pre tabindex="0" style="color:#f8f8f2;background-color:#272822;-moz-tab-size:4;-o-tab-size:4;tab-size:4;-webkit-text-size-adjust:none;"&gt;&lt;code class="language-javascript" data-lang="javascript"&gt;&lt;span style="display:flex;"&gt;&lt;span&gt;&lt;span style="color:#66d9ef"&gt;const&lt;/span&gt; &lt;span style="color:#a6e22e"&gt;net&lt;/span&gt; &lt;span style="color:#f92672"&gt;=&lt;/span&gt; &lt;span style="color:#a6e22e"&gt;require&lt;/span&gt;(&lt;span style="color:#e6db74"&gt;&amp;#34;node:net&amp;#34;&lt;/span&gt;);
&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span style="display:flex;"&gt;&lt;span&gt;
&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span style="display:flex;"&gt;&lt;span&gt;&lt;span style="color:#66d9ef"&gt;const&lt;/span&gt; &lt;span style="color:#a6e22e"&gt;server&lt;/span&gt; &lt;span style="color:#f92672"&gt;=&lt;/span&gt; &lt;span style="color:#a6e22e"&gt;net&lt;/span&gt;.&lt;span style="color:#a6e22e"&gt;createServer&lt;/span&gt;();
&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span style="display:flex;"&gt;&lt;span&gt;&lt;span style="color:#a6e22e"&gt;server&lt;/span&gt;.&lt;span style="color:#a6e22e"&gt;on&lt;/span&gt;(&lt;span style="color:#e6db74"&gt;&amp;#34;error&amp;#34;&lt;/span&gt;, (&lt;span style="color:#a6e22e"&gt;err&lt;/span&gt;) =&amp;gt; {
&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span style="display:flex;"&gt;&lt;span&gt; &lt;span style="color:#a6e22e"&gt;console&lt;/span&gt;.&lt;span style="color:#a6e22e"&gt;error&lt;/span&gt;(&lt;span style="color:#e6db74"&gt;&amp;#34;Server error:&amp;#34;&lt;/span&gt;, &lt;span style="color:#a6e22e"&gt;err&lt;/span&gt;.&lt;span style="color:#a6e22e"&gt;message&lt;/span&gt;);
&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span style="display:flex;"&gt;&lt;span&gt;});
&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span style="display:flex;"&gt;&lt;span&gt;
&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span style="display:flex;"&gt;&lt;span&gt;&lt;span style="color:#75715e"&gt;// Set SO_REUSEADDR before binding
&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span style="display:flex;"&gt;&lt;span&gt;&lt;span style="color:#a6e22e"&gt;server&lt;/span&gt;.&lt;span style="color:#a6e22e"&gt;listen&lt;/span&gt;({ &lt;span style="color:#a6e22e"&gt;port&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span style="color:#f92672"&gt;:&lt;/span&gt; &lt;span style="color:#ae81ff"&gt;3000&lt;/span&gt;, &lt;span style="color:#a6e22e"&gt;exclusive&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span style="color:#f92672"&gt;:&lt;/span&gt; &lt;span style="color:#66d9ef"&gt;false&lt;/span&gt; });
&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/code&gt;&lt;/pre&gt;&lt;/div&gt;&lt;h2 id="examples"&gt;Examples&lt;/h2&gt;
&lt;div class="highlight"&gt;&lt;pre tabindex="0" style="color:#f8f8f2;background-color:#272822;-moz-tab-size:4;-o-tab-size:4;tab-size:4;-webkit-text-size-adjust:none;"&gt;&lt;code class="language-javascript" data-lang="javascript"&gt;&lt;span style="display:flex;"&gt;&lt;span&gt;&lt;span style="color:#75715e"&gt;// EADDRINUSE: port 3000 already in use
&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span style="display:flex;"&gt;&lt;span&gt;&lt;span style="color:#75715e"&gt;// $ lsof -i :3000
&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span style="display:flex;"&gt;&lt;span&gt;&lt;span style="color:#75715e"&gt;// COMMAND PID USER FD TYPE DEVICE SIZE/OFF NODE NAME
&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span style="display:flex;"&gt;&lt;span&gt;&lt;span style="color:#75715e"&gt;// node 12345 admin 20u IPv6 ... 0t0 TCP *:3000 (LISTEN)
&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span style="display:flex;"&gt;&lt;span&gt;&lt;span style="color:#75715e"&gt;// $ kill 12345
&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span style="display:flex;"&gt;&lt;span&gt;&lt;span style="color:#75715e"&gt;// $ node server.js (now it works)
&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/code&gt;&lt;/pre&gt;&lt;/div&gt;&lt;h2 id="related-errors"&gt;Related Errors&lt;/h2&gt;
&lt;ul&gt;
&lt;li&gt;&lt;a href="https://errorcode.excellentwiki.com/languages/javascript/err_http_headers_sent/"&gt;ERR_HTTP_SERVER_RESPONSE&lt;/a&gt; — HTTP response error.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;&lt;a href="https://errorcode.excellentwiki.com/languages/javascript/err_stream_destroyed/"&gt;ERR_STREAM_DESTROYED&lt;/a&gt; — stream destroyed before operation completes.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;&lt;a href="https://errorcode.excellentwiki.com/languages/javascript/err_socket_destroyed/"&gt;ERR_SOCKET_DESTROYED&lt;/a&gt; — socket destroyed.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;/ul&gt;</description></item><item><title>SSR Server Component Error</title><link>https://errorcode.excellentwiki.com/tools/vite/ssr-error/</link><pubDate>Mon, 01 Jan 0001 00:00:00 +0000</pubDate><guid>https://errorcode.excellentwiki.com/tools/vite/ssr-error/</guid><description>&lt;p&gt;This error means Vite&amp;rsquo;s SSR module runner failed while executing code on the server. It typically surfaces when a component or module throws during server-side rendering.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;h2 id="common-causes"&gt;Common Causes&lt;/h2&gt;
&lt;ul&gt;
&lt;li&gt;A browser-only API (like &lt;code&gt;window&lt;/code&gt; or &lt;code&gt;document&lt;/code&gt;) is used in server-rendered code&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;A dependency is not compatible with SSR environments&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Import path issues when Vite resolves server and client bundles separately&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Circular dependencies in server-side modules&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;/ul&gt;
&lt;h2 id="how-to-fix"&gt;How to Fix&lt;/h2&gt;
&lt;p&gt;Guard browser-only code with environment checks:&lt;/p&gt;</description></item><item><title>[Solution] Ruby Errno::EADDRINUSE — Address Already in Use Fix</title><link>https://errorcode.excellentwiki.com/languages/ruby/address-in-use/</link><pubDate>Mon, 01 Jan 0001 00:00:00 +0000</pubDate><guid>https://errorcode.excellentwiki.com/languages/ruby/address-in-use/</guid><description>&lt;h1 id="errnoeaddrinuse--address-already-in-use-fix"&gt;Errno::EADDRINUSE — Address Already in Use Fix&lt;/h1&gt;
&lt;p&gt;An &lt;code&gt;Errno::EADDRINUSE&lt;/code&gt; is raised when trying to bind to a port or address that&amp;rsquo;s already in use by another process.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;h2 id="description"&gt;Description&lt;/h2&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;code&gt;Errno::EADDRINUSE&lt;/code&gt; means the port or address you&amp;rsquo;re trying to use is already bound by another socket. This is common when starting servers.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;Common scenarios:&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;ul&gt;
&lt;li&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Server already running&lt;/strong&gt; — another instance is using the port.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Port in TIME_WAIT&lt;/strong&gt; — previous connection hasn&amp;rsquo;t fully closed.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Wrong bind address&lt;/strong&gt; — trying to bind to a specific IP that&amp;rsquo;s taken.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;&lt;strong&gt;SO_REUSEADDR not set&lt;/strong&gt; — socket option not configured.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;/ul&gt;
&lt;h2 id="common-causes"&gt;Common Causes&lt;/h2&gt;
&lt;div class="highlight"&gt;&lt;pre tabindex="0" style="color:#f8f8f2;background-color:#272822;-moz-tab-size:4;-o-tab-size:4;tab-size:4;-webkit-text-size-adjust:none;"&gt;&lt;code class="language-ruby" data-lang="ruby"&gt;&lt;span style="display:flex;"&gt;&lt;span&gt;&lt;span style="color:#75715e"&gt;# Cause 1: Server already running&lt;/span&gt;
&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span style="display:flex;"&gt;&lt;span&gt;server &lt;span style="color:#f92672"&gt;=&lt;/span&gt; &lt;span style="color:#66d9ef"&gt;TCPServer&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span style="color:#f92672"&gt;.&lt;/span&gt;new(&lt;span style="color:#e6db74"&gt;&amp;#34;0.0.0.0&amp;#34;&lt;/span&gt;, &lt;span style="color:#ae81ff"&gt;8080&lt;/span&gt;) &lt;span style="color:#75715e"&gt;# Errno::EADDRINUSE&lt;/span&gt;
&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span style="display:flex;"&gt;&lt;span&gt;
&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span style="display:flex;"&gt;&lt;span&gt;&lt;span style="color:#75715e"&gt;# Cause 2: Port in TIME_WAIT state&lt;/span&gt;
&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span style="display:flex;"&gt;&lt;span&gt;&lt;span style="color:#75715e"&gt;# Previous server instance closed but port not released yet&lt;/span&gt;
&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span style="display:flex;"&gt;&lt;span&gt;
&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span style="display:flex;"&gt;&lt;span&gt;&lt;span style="color:#75715e"&gt;# Cause 3: Another process using the port&lt;/span&gt;
&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span style="display:flex;"&gt;&lt;span&gt;&lt;span style="color:#75715e"&gt;# Different application listening on same port&lt;/span&gt;
&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span style="display:flex;"&gt;&lt;span&gt;
&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span style="display:flex;"&gt;&lt;span&gt;&lt;span style="color:#75715e"&gt;# Cause 4: Trying to bind to both 0.0.0.0 and specific IP&lt;/span&gt;
&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span style="display:flex;"&gt;&lt;span&gt;&lt;span style="color:#75715e"&gt;# Already bound to 0.0.0.0:8080, trying 127.0.0.1:8080&lt;/span&gt;
&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/code&gt;&lt;/pre&gt;&lt;/div&gt;&lt;h2 id="solutions"&gt;Solutions&lt;/h2&gt;
&lt;h3 id="fix-1-check-if-port-is-in-use"&gt;Fix 1: Check if port is in use&lt;/h3&gt;
&lt;div class="highlight"&gt;&lt;pre tabindex="0" style="color:#f8f8f2;background-color:#272822;-moz-tab-size:4;-o-tab-size:4;tab-size:4;-webkit-text-size-adjust:none;"&gt;&lt;code class="language-ruby" data-lang="ruby"&gt;&lt;span style="display:flex;"&gt;&lt;span&gt;&lt;span style="color:#66d9ef"&gt;def&lt;/span&gt; &lt;span style="color:#a6e22e"&gt;port_in_use?&lt;/span&gt;(port)
&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span style="display:flex;"&gt;&lt;span&gt; &lt;span style="color:#66d9ef"&gt;begin&lt;/span&gt;
&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span style="display:flex;"&gt;&lt;span&gt; server &lt;span style="color:#f92672"&gt;=&lt;/span&gt; &lt;span style="color:#66d9ef"&gt;TCPServer&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span style="color:#f92672"&gt;.&lt;/span&gt;new(&lt;span style="color:#e6db74"&gt;&amp;#34;0.0.0.0&amp;#34;&lt;/span&gt;, port)
&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span style="display:flex;"&gt;&lt;span&gt; server&lt;span style="color:#f92672"&gt;.&lt;/span&gt;close
&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span style="display:flex;"&gt;&lt;span&gt; &lt;span style="color:#66d9ef"&gt;false&lt;/span&gt;
&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span style="display:flex;"&gt;&lt;span&gt; &lt;span style="color:#66d9ef"&gt;rescue&lt;/span&gt; &lt;span style="color:#66d9ef"&gt;Errno&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span style="color:#f92672"&gt;::&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span style="color:#66d9ef"&gt;EADDRINUSE&lt;/span&gt;
&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span style="display:flex;"&gt;&lt;span&gt; &lt;span style="color:#66d9ef"&gt;true&lt;/span&gt;
&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span style="display:flex;"&gt;&lt;span&gt; &lt;span style="color:#66d9ef"&gt;end&lt;/span&gt;
&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span style="display:flex;"&gt;&lt;span&gt;&lt;span style="color:#66d9ef"&gt;end&lt;/span&gt;
&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span style="display:flex;"&gt;&lt;span&gt;
&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span style="display:flex;"&gt;&lt;span&gt;&lt;span style="color:#66d9ef"&gt;if&lt;/span&gt; port_in_use?(&lt;span style="color:#ae81ff"&gt;8080&lt;/span&gt;)
&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span style="display:flex;"&gt;&lt;span&gt; puts &lt;span style="color:#e6db74"&gt;&amp;#34;Port 8080 is already in use&amp;#34;&lt;/span&gt;
&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span style="display:flex;"&gt;&lt;span&gt;&lt;span style="color:#66d9ef"&gt;else&lt;/span&gt;
&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span style="display:flex;"&gt;&lt;span&gt; server &lt;span style="color:#f92672"&gt;=&lt;/span&gt; &lt;span style="color:#66d9ef"&gt;TCPServer&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span style="color:#f92672"&gt;.&lt;/span&gt;new(&lt;span style="color:#e6db74"&gt;&amp;#34;0.0.0.0&amp;#34;&lt;/span&gt;, &lt;span style="color:#ae81ff"&gt;8080&lt;/span&gt;)
&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span style="display:flex;"&gt;&lt;span&gt;&lt;span style="color:#66d9ef"&gt;end&lt;/span&gt;
&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/code&gt;&lt;/pre&gt;&lt;/div&gt;&lt;h3 id="fix-2-use-so_reuseaddr"&gt;Fix 2: Use SO_REUSEADDR&lt;/h3&gt;
&lt;div class="highlight"&gt;&lt;pre tabindex="0" style="color:#f8f8f2;background-color:#272822;-moz-tab-size:4;-o-tab-size:4;tab-size:4;-webkit-text-size-adjust:none;"&gt;&lt;code class="language-ruby" data-lang="ruby"&gt;&lt;span style="display:flex;"&gt;&lt;span&gt;require &lt;span style="color:#e6db74"&gt;&amp;#39;socket&amp;#39;&lt;/span&gt;
&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span style="display:flex;"&gt;&lt;span&gt;
&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span style="display:flex;"&gt;&lt;span&gt;server &lt;span style="color:#f92672"&gt;=&lt;/span&gt; &lt;span style="color:#66d9ef"&gt;TCPServer&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span style="color:#f92672"&gt;.&lt;/span&gt;new(&lt;span style="color:#e6db74"&gt;&amp;#34;0.0.0.0&amp;#34;&lt;/span&gt;, &lt;span style="color:#ae81ff"&gt;8080&lt;/span&gt;)
&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span style="display:flex;"&gt;&lt;span&gt;server&lt;span style="color:#f92672"&gt;.&lt;/span&gt;setsockopt(&lt;span style="color:#66d9ef"&gt;Socket&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span style="color:#f92672"&gt;::&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span style="color:#66d9ef"&gt;SOL_SOCKET&lt;/span&gt;, &lt;span style="color:#66d9ef"&gt;Socket&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span style="color:#f92672"&gt;::&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span style="color:#66d9ef"&gt;SO_REUSEADDR&lt;/span&gt;, &lt;span style="color:#ae81ff"&gt;1&lt;/span&gt;)
&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/code&gt;&lt;/pre&gt;&lt;/div&gt;&lt;h3 id="fix-3-kill-existing-process-using-the-port"&gt;Fix 3: Kill existing process using the port&lt;/h3&gt;
&lt;div class="highlight"&gt;&lt;pre tabindex="0" style="color:#f8f8f2;background-color:#272822;-moz-tab-size:4;-o-tab-size:4;tab-size:4;-webkit-text-size-adjust:none;"&gt;&lt;code class="language-bash" data-lang="bash"&gt;&lt;span style="display:flex;"&gt;&lt;span&gt;&lt;span style="color:#75715e"&gt;# Find process using port 8080&lt;/span&gt;
&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span style="display:flex;"&gt;&lt;span&gt;lsof -i :8080
&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span style="display:flex;"&gt;&lt;span&gt;
&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span style="display:flex;"&gt;&lt;span&gt;&lt;span style="color:#75715e"&gt;# Or use netstat&lt;/span&gt;
&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span style="display:flex;"&gt;&lt;span&gt;netstat -tlnp | grep &lt;span style="color:#ae81ff"&gt;8080&lt;/span&gt;
&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span style="display:flex;"&gt;&lt;span&gt;
&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span style="display:flex;"&gt;&lt;span&gt;&lt;span style="color:#75715e"&gt;# Kill the process&lt;/span&gt;
&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span style="display:flex;"&gt;&lt;span&gt;kill -9 &amp;lt;PID&amp;gt;
&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/code&gt;&lt;/pre&gt;&lt;/div&gt;&lt;h3 id="fix-4-wait-and-retry"&gt;Fix 4: Wait and retry&lt;/h3&gt;
&lt;div class="highlight"&gt;&lt;pre tabindex="0" style="color:#f8f8f2;background-color:#272822;-moz-tab-size:4;-o-tab-size:4;tab-size:4;-webkit-text-size-adjust:none;"&gt;&lt;code class="language-ruby" data-lang="ruby"&gt;&lt;span style="display:flex;"&gt;&lt;span&gt;&lt;span style="color:#66d9ef"&gt;def&lt;/span&gt; &lt;span style="color:#a6e22e"&gt;start_server&lt;/span&gt;(port, retries &lt;span style="color:#f92672"&gt;=&lt;/span&gt; &lt;span style="color:#ae81ff"&gt;5&lt;/span&gt;)
&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span style="display:flex;"&gt;&lt;span&gt; retries&lt;span style="color:#f92672"&gt;.&lt;/span&gt;times &lt;span style="color:#66d9ef"&gt;do&lt;/span&gt; &lt;span style="color:#f92672"&gt;|&lt;/span&gt;i&lt;span style="color:#f92672"&gt;|&lt;/span&gt;
&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span style="display:flex;"&gt;&lt;span&gt; &lt;span style="color:#66d9ef"&gt;begin&lt;/span&gt;
&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span style="display:flex;"&gt;&lt;span&gt; &lt;span style="color:#66d9ef"&gt;return&lt;/span&gt; &lt;span style="color:#66d9ef"&gt;TCPServer&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span style="color:#f92672"&gt;.&lt;/span&gt;new(&lt;span style="color:#e6db74"&gt;&amp;#34;0.0.0.0&amp;#34;&lt;/span&gt;, port)
&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span style="display:flex;"&gt;&lt;span&gt; &lt;span style="color:#66d9ef"&gt;rescue&lt;/span&gt; &lt;span style="color:#66d9ef"&gt;Errno&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span style="color:#f92672"&gt;::&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span style="color:#66d9ef"&gt;EADDRINUSE&lt;/span&gt;
&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span style="display:flex;"&gt;&lt;span&gt; puts &lt;span style="color:#e6db74"&gt;&amp;#34;Port &lt;/span&gt;&lt;span style="color:#e6db74"&gt;#{&lt;/span&gt;port&lt;span style="color:#e6db74"&gt;}&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span style="color:#e6db74"&gt; in use, retrying in &lt;/span&gt;&lt;span style="color:#e6db74"&gt;#{&lt;/span&gt;i &lt;span style="color:#f92672"&gt;+&lt;/span&gt; &lt;span style="color:#ae81ff"&gt;1&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span style="color:#e6db74"&gt;}&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span style="color:#e6db74"&gt; seconds...&amp;#34;&lt;/span&gt;
&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span style="display:flex;"&gt;&lt;span&gt; sleep(i &lt;span style="color:#f92672"&gt;+&lt;/span&gt; &lt;span style="color:#ae81ff"&gt;1&lt;/span&gt;)
&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span style="display:flex;"&gt;&lt;span&gt; &lt;span style="color:#66d9ef"&gt;end&lt;/span&gt;
&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span style="display:flex;"&gt;&lt;span&gt; &lt;span style="color:#66d9ef"&gt;end&lt;/span&gt;
&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span style="display:flex;"&gt;&lt;span&gt; &lt;span style="color:#66d9ef"&gt;raise&lt;/span&gt; &lt;span style="color:#e6db74"&gt;&amp;#34;Could not bind to port &lt;/span&gt;&lt;span style="color:#e6db74"&gt;#{&lt;/span&gt;port&lt;span style="color:#e6db74"&gt;}&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span style="color:#e6db74"&gt; after &lt;/span&gt;&lt;span style="color:#e6db74"&gt;#{&lt;/span&gt;retries&lt;span style="color:#e6db74"&gt;}&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span style="color:#e6db74"&gt; retries&amp;#34;&lt;/span&gt;
&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span style="display:flex;"&gt;&lt;span&gt;&lt;span style="color:#66d9ef"&gt;end&lt;/span&gt;
&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/code&gt;&lt;/pre&gt;&lt;/div&gt;&lt;h2 id="related-errors"&gt;Related Errors&lt;/h2&gt;
&lt;ul&gt;
&lt;li&gt;&lt;a href="connection-refused"&gt;Errno::ECONNREFUSED&lt;/a&gt; — connection refused.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;&lt;a href="broken-pipe"&gt;Errno::EPIPE&lt;/a&gt; — broken pipe.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;&lt;a href="io-error"&gt;IOError&lt;/a&gt; — stream closed or invalid I/O.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;/ul&gt;</description></item></channel></rss>